14/04/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Minister of Public Order Igli Toska and his visiting Greek counterpart, Georgios Voulgarakis, will meet Wednesday (14 April) to discuss co-operation, especially regarding security during the upcoming Summer Olympics in Athens.
This will be the first visit to Albania by a minister of the New Democracy Party, which won the March elections in Greece.
In other news, Defence Minister Pandeli Majko and his Romanian counterpart, Ioan Mircea Pascu, met on Tuesday and reiterated their commitment to the coalition mission in Iraq.
They also discussed bilateral co-operation in the fields of defence and regional security and shared experiences in implementing army reforms.
(ATA, MPA, Rompres - 13/04/04)
